orkers are not covered.\nThose who receive old-aye and survivors\u2019 insurance\nhcucllls receive an payment of only a\nmonth. Many others who cannot work because they\nare physically disabled are left to the mercy ol\neha rit y.\nWe should expand our social security proyram,\nboth as to si/.c of benefits and extent ot coverage,\nayaitist the economic hazards dm* to unemployment,\nold aye. si*-kilevs and disability.\nWe must spare no effort to raise the yeneral level\nof health in this country. In a nation as rich as\nours. it is a shocking fact that fens ol millions lack\nadequate medical cere. W c air short ot doctors, hos\npitals and 1111 I s s.\nWe must remedy these shortages. Moreover, we\nneed and we must have without further delay a\nsystem of prepaid medical insurance which will en\nable everv American to afford yood medical care.\n\nOil Aid to Kdiicalion\nI cannot repeat Inn stronylv my <I s i 1 for prompt\nlednal financial aid to the states to help them upd\nate an d maintain tin 11 scho<\u2022l s\\ s|enis.\nOil (!i\\ iI l{iglits\nIhe civ 1 1 r 1 y 1 1 1 s proposals I made to the MM h(o 11\ny 1 css I now m pea t I o t lie S| sf ony 1 ess. Tin V sho 11 Id\nl*c enacted in order that the federal government may\nassume the leadership and discharyr the oM 1 y .l l ion 4\n<-1 ca\u00bb I placed upon it by Ihe oust it lit ion.\nI stand squa lel beli md these pioposals.\nOil Housing\n'I he in y short ay c continues to be acute. A s an\nimmediate step, the I onyress should Marl plo\\ 1-\nsnuis lor low lent public hoiisiuy. slum dcaiauce,\nfaim boiisiny, and luuisiny research, which I have\n1 c| tea t c\u00bb 11 v rect im mended.\nThe number of low rent public hoiisiuy unils pro\nvided for in the legislation should be increased to\none million units in the next seven years.\nOn Foreign Policy\nWe are following a foreign policy w hich is ihe\noutward expression of the democratic faith we pro\nfess. We are doing what we ran to encourage free\nslates and free peoples throughout the world, to aid\nthe suffering and afflicted in foreiyn lands, and to\nsi reiiy 1 lien democratic nations ayainsl aggression.\nThe heart of our foreiyn policy is peaee. We are\nsupporting a world organization to keep peace ami\na world economic policy to create prosperity for all\nmankind. Our yuidiny star is the principle of inter\nnational cooperation. To this concept wc have made\na national commitment as profound as anything ill\nhistory.\nIn the Kuropean Kceovery I Yog mm. in our yood\nneighbor policy and in the I idled Nations, we have\nbegun to batter down those national walls which\nblock the economic growth and the social advance\nment of the peoples of the world.\nWe believe that if wc hold resolutely to this course,\nthe principle of international cooperation will even\ntually command the approval even of those nations*\nwhich are now seeking to weaken or subvert it.\nPage 9","height":"29793","width":"20028"}}
